                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>Cigarettes</Header>
                <Paragraph>The FDA describes cigarettes with three words: attractive, addictive, and deadly. Cigarettes are designed to be attractive and addictive. The FDA's infographic "How a Cigarette is Engineered" explains the role design plays in attraction and addiction.</Paragraph>
            </EntitySourceOfInformation>
